You need two pieces: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` and **`BackButtonBehavior`** on the page.

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage`

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

In the view model:

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    if (HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 2. Guard the hardware/swipe back in `AppShell`

The `CancelCommand` handles the button, but hardware back and swipe gestures bypass it. Guard those in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **`GetDeferral()`** is required because the confirmation is async â€” without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so the guard only fires on back navigation, not forward pushes.
- The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` intercepts the Shell back button; `OnNavigating` catches hardware/swipe back. Together they cover all paths.
